cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with 3D medical image segmentation using convolutional neural networks. It also involves neural architecture search (NAS), which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper proposes a new method for NAS, which could be relevant to the neural evolution (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its method on public datasets, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
